DOCUMENT();

loadMacros('PGstandard.pl', 'PGML.pl', 'PGcourse.pl');

#  Setup

Context("Numeric")->variables->are(t => Real);

$a           = random(2000, 2500, 10);
$rpercent    = random(-3.9, -3.1, 0.1);
$rpercentpos = -($rpercent);
$r           = $rpercent / 100;
$b           = 1 + $r;

$f = Formula("$a * ($b)**t");

BEGIN_PGML

Find a formula for [` P = f(t) `], the  size of the population that begins in year
[` t = 0 `] with [` [$a] `] members and decreases at a [` [$rpercentpos] `]%  annual
rate.  Assume that time is measured in years.

[` P = f(t) = `] [_]{$f}{20}


END_PGML

BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION

The starting value is [`a=[$a]`]. The growth rate is [`r=[$r]`]% (note that it is negative), 
so [`b=1+r=[$b]`]. The formula is 

[```P = [$f]```]

END_PGML_SOLUTION

ENDDOCUMENT();
